<br>

<span style="font-family:Centaur; color:#F50A0A; text-shadow: 0 0 20px #850505">''The snow hides everything...doesn't it? It can hide everything, even humanities greatest sins. The snow is an empty canvas on top of a painting. The paint however is not paint, but rather bits upon bits of sins that grow more by the second. The snow can hide it all, but it can as easily be uncovered. ...But do I really want to open the art, or should I just let it stay buried?}}''


==<span style="font-family:Grotesk; color:#F50A0A; text-shadow: 0 0 10px #850505">'''''Description'''''</span>==

'''Level 373''' is a level covered in snow with varying layers of depth. The ground beneath the snow is entirely red and can immediately scorch one's self almost instantaneously. This effect, however, does not extend to some objects that the wanderer holds. It is random, however, as to what the object can be, as most objects the wanderer is holding will burn with them if they touch the red ground.

The vast majority of the level is a mountainous region, while some portions are flat ground. There are no known buildings in the mountains themselves. There are, however, certain buildings in the flat areas of the level. These buildings appear to be 1960s Cold War-era Soviet buildings intended for research, as evidenced by the files and equipment found in the buildings. It is unknown how the buildings are in the level, however, but it is suspected that they are connected to the entity in this level based on a single piece of writing that appears on a random piece of wall in every single building.
{{Blurimage|file=Save us.png|caption=Building in '''Level 373'''|align=right}}
<span style="font-family:Centaur; color:#F50A0A; text-shadow: 0 0 20px #850505">"Спаси нас, о дорогой бог, облаченный в красное и белое. Мы ищем спасения от бесконечной войны и страданий, которые навлекли на нас наши лидеры. Позволь нам заключить тебя в твои вечно милосердные объятия и позволить тебе привести нас в обещанное ледяное царство, о котором ты проповедуешь."</span> 

(Save us, O dear god, clothed in red and white. We are seeking salvation from the endless war and suffering that our leaders have brought upon us. Let us embrace you in your ever-merciful embrace and let you lead us to the promised kingdom of ice that you preach about.) 

{{Collapse|num=2|initial=<u>'''Down into the depths of his domain.'''</u>|final='''<u>Did they make a deal or not?</u>|body=
<br>

<span style="font-family:Centaur; color:#F50A0A; text-shadow: 0 0 20px #850505">''Here I am, at the one of many bridges that lead to the center of whatever this place is. As I cross the bridge, I notice the place is all covered in snow...but yet we are underground. I wonder if this is his work. But from what I see, the red ground extends to here as well, so I also must be very careful here as well. As I enter these apartments and houses are all...different? Looks like a mix of different houses, buildings from different countries...different years.''


<span style="font-family:Centaur; color:#F50A0A; text-shadow: 0 0 20px #850505">''...In all the houses, all the buildings that are here, there are various statues of either a single person or multiple people. ...Did these people make a deal with him? Did these people commit any types of sins? ...Whatever they did, I am sure it is related to him, deal or not.}}''

===<span style="font-family:Grotesk; color:#F50A0A; text-shadow: 0 0 10px #850505">'''''The City of Red and White'''''</span>===

In the mountain regions of '''Level 373''', there are many caves that go into the mountains. Most of these caves however have an entirely red surface, preventing most people from going in there. There are however a few cases that have snow surrounding the entire cave. These caves are safe to enter and walk through. Eventually will lead to a bridge made of ice. Cross that bridge, and one will enter the city.
{{Blurimage|file=Ice House.jpg|caption=Image of an Ice House in '''Level 373'''.|align=right}}
The city itself is a mix of both older and newer buildings from various years and various different parts of the world. These buildings mostly contain of solid snow but have elements of red materials on various surfaces. The red material is exactly the same as that of the red ground. Inside the houses/buildings themselves, one will find everything frozen in place and cannot be moved. They will also find either a person or multiple frozen people inside of the houses/buildings. It is thought however that these are just replicas of the people that resided in these structures and are not actually the people themselves.

Inside the city are giant stone fountains, which due to the frozen nature of the level, do not function. Inside the fountains however are a bunch of red text in various languages, many of which are in Russian. All of these texts, when translated, praises an entity in red and white.


A few examples of the texts are: <span style="font-family:Centaur; color:#F50A0A; text-shadow: 0 0 20px #850505">"О, спаси нас, великий царь, ибо мы ищем спасения от этого мира войн и болезней."</span> ("Oh, save us, great king, for we seek salvation from this world of wars and diseases.")<span style="font-family:Centaur; color:#F50A0A; text-shadow: 0 0 20px #850505">"Нашему Красному и Белому богу, пожалуйста, отведи нас в свою землю обетованную, где мы будем петь тебе хвалу."</span> ("To our Red and White God, please take us to your promised land, where we will sing your praises.") <span style="font-family:Centaur; color:#F50A0A; text-shadow: 0 0 20px #850505">"Нашему Господу и спасителю, услышьте наши хвалебные песни только для вас. Мы всегда будем в долгу перед вашей милостью и надеемся, что вы сможете обеспечить нас всем необходимым." </span> ("To our Lord and Savior, hear our songs of praise just for you. We will always be indebted to Your Grace and hope that you will be able to provide us with everything we need.")

===<span style="font-family:Grotesk; color:#F50A0A; text-shadow: 0 0 10px #850505">'''''The Castle'''''</span>===

{{Collapse|num=3|initial=<u>'''Down into the depths of his domain.'''</u>|final='''<u>His domain lies in the center.</u>|body=
<br>

<span style="font-family:Centaur; color:#F50A0A; text-shadow: 0 0 20px #850505">''I entered into what I suspected what was his domain. It is in in the center and certainly not from modern times, not even in the last century alone. It was...unusual in a sense. All throughout the other bits of this land was snow on a scorching red surface. But his home...his castle, was different. There was no signs of snow at all. In fact it was luxurious, quite unusual in a land of frozen ruin.''}}
{{Blurimage|file=Frigid Castle.png|caption=Image of the interior of the castle in '''Level 404'''.|align=right}}
The Castle is in the center of the city of red and white, and unlike the rest of '''Level 373''', does not appeared to be covered in snow nor has any red surfaces that can scorch one's self. The outside of the castle has a medieval-like appearance, with bricks surrounding the exterior of the castle. On these bricks are also the names of certain people, with the date of when they were born and when they supposedly died. It is speculated however that these are not death dates, but rather when they made a deal with the entity in red and white.

The inside of the castle is vastly different than the outside, as instead of bricks or any other details on the outside of the castle, it takes on the appearance of a Victorian mansion. The interior however is very dim, with very few lights active at any given time. The majority of the inside of the castle is living rooms with a few scattered pieces of furniture around, but rarely there will be other rooms like kitchens, bathrooms, and even bedrooms. But none of these rooms have any uses outside of the bedroom however, as the kitchen does not have any food or drinks and the waters inside the bathroom are frozen.


==<span style="font-family:Grotesk; color:#F50A0A; text-shadow: 0 0 10px #850505">'''''Entities'''''</span>==


===<span style="font-family:Grotesk; color:#F50A0A; text-shadow: 0 0 10px #850505">'''''The Devil in Red and White'''''</span>===


The Devil in Red and White is the only entity in '''Level 373'''. He is an entity that wears a cloak of red and white. The cloak is however the only visible part of him. Those who see him describe him as just a floating being, and when they attempt to see what his face looks like, they claim that they see "The Universe Itself" within him. Those who do look within his "face", feel a sense of both total euphoria and total paranoia at the same time.  

When one initiates a conversation with the devil in red and white, they will be asked if they wish to make a deal with him. If they do not wish to, he will leave them alone. As a result of not wanting to make a deal however, all exits will suddenly not work for them and as a result, they will die within the level due to dehydration unless they touch the red ground outside the castle. They will also not be able to see the devil in red and white again as well.

If one accepts to make a deal with him however, they will be led to the closest living room unless they are in one already. The devil in red and white will give them time to think of what they truly want. He will however encourage them to think, as he says that any deals will come at a cost. 

When one has given thought to what they truly desire, the devil in red and white will grant them their wish. They do not even have to say anything, for the devil knows what they are thinking of. When the wish is granted, there will be a brief flash of white light. When the light fades, the devil will be nowhere to be seen and cannot be seen again to those who have had their wishes granted. 

{{Collapse|num=4|initial=<u>'''A wolf in sheep's clothing.'''</u>|final='''<u>He is the savior of few, devil of many.</u>|body=
<br>

<span style="font-family:Centaur; color:#F50A0A; text-shadow: 0 0 20px #850505">''I saw the houses and the fountains and even his castle, and there is no doubt he is perhaps a god of some kind. Some may call him a king, but he is certainly a king with the elements of God. But this god is not the good kind. If anything, he is a false god, constructing himself as a false hope to those who are desperate for escape. In that essence, he is not a god at all, but rather a devil. He is a devil in god's clothing.''


<span style="font-family:Centaur; color:#F50A0A; text-shadow: 0 0 20px #850505">''He offered deals to those who were desperate enough, to those who had nowhere else to turn. To most, he is the devil himself. But to some...he their lord and savior. Those poor souls...but it's too late for them. I can only hope others see through his tricks, wherever he may pop-up next.}}''

==<span style="font-family:Grotesk; color:#F50A0A; text-shadow: 0 0 10px #850505">'''''Groups and Organizations'''''</span>==

Due to this level's inhospitable nature and unpredictability, establishment of any bases or outposts in '''Level 373''' are not possible. Despite the aforementioned details however, there is a group of 12 people who live in '''Level 373'''.

===<span style="font-family:Grotesk; color:#F50A0A; text-shadow: 0 0 10px #850505">'''''The 12 Sons'''''</span>===

The 12 Sons are a group of twelve human beings who have devoted themselves to the devil in red and white. They all wear cloaks similar to the "King" they worship, except they each numbered their cloaks 1-12 to differentiate themselves from whom they worship in order to respect him. They are neutral in terms of who they meet and will answer questions whenever they are asked something. Any negative mentions of the devil in red and white however will result in them being hostile and will kill anyone who badmouths them or the one they worship.  

They explain that they are a group of former cold war scientists and solders who sought escape from the [[The Frontrooms|real world]] as they grew to view that world negatively and sought to escape that world. They say the found one day an abandoned village in the frozen Siberian wilderness and found symbols and texts in Russian about a king in red and white. They studied and copied the symbols and texts they found. They brough back that research to their base and shared it with two other remote Siberian outposts. When they attempted to find the abandoned village again however, they found no traces of it at all despite being in the exact same location. 

Soon after seeing the village was no longer there, they say that they began to see visions of everything that ever was. They see each scientist began seeing moments of history, even one claiming that they saw the birth of the universe. Soon enough, they said that their "King" came to them and made a deal with them. In exchange for permanent residence in his kingdom and immortal life, they were to serve him until the end of time. And they say they have not regretted a single moment since.


==<span style="font-family:Grotesk; color:#F50A0A; text-shadow: 0 0 10px #850505">'''''Entrances and Exits'''''</span>==


===<span style="font-family:Grotesk; color:#F50A0A; text-shadow: 0 0 10px #850505">'''''Entrances'''''</span>===

In [[Level 202]], if one finds an out-of-place red snowy glacier and touches it, they will be brought here.

In [[Level 505]], if one manages to find a book titled "Life And Death" in the library and open that book, they will be brought here.

In [[Level 303]], if one manages to find text reading "I can be your savior." in red, and reads it aloud, they will be brought here.


===<span style="font-family:Grotesk; color:#F50A0A; text-shadow: 0 0 10px #850505">'''''Exits'''''</span>===

All exits can only be accessed by making a deal with the devil in red and white, otherwise one stuck in '''Level 373'''.

If one goes to bed in one of the bedrooms, they will wake up in [[Level 909]].

If one leaves the city and attempts to go back through the tunnel to the mountain ranges above, they will instead end up in [[Level 44]].

